      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 634: Using `getConversations().empty()` as the only guard means accounts that legitimately have zero conversations will re-run `initContacts()` and `initConversations()` on every TRYING/REGISTERED status transition. That can trigger repeated daemon calls/signals and makes the reload non-idempotent despite the comment. Please guard this with an explicit loaded/initialized state instead of the current list size, or mark the refresh as attempted once it succeeds.\n```suggestion\n            if ((status \u003d\u003d api::account::Status::TRYING || status \u003d\u003d api::account::Status::REGISTERED)\n                \u0026\u0026 !accountInfo.conversationsInitialized) {\n                accountInfo.contactModel-\u003einitContacts();\n                accountInfo.conversationModel-\u003einitConversations();\n                accountInfo.conversationsInitialized \u003d true;\n            }\n```",
